==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Relict
<hw>Rel"ict</hw> <pr>(-?kt)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>relicta</ets>, fr. of <ets>relictus</ets>, p. p. of
<ets>relinquere</ets> to leave behind. See <er>Relinquish</er>.]</ety>
<def>A woman whose husband is dead; a widow.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Eli dying without issue, Jacob was obliged by law to marry his
<qex>relict</qex>, and so to raise up seed to his brother Eli.</q>
<rj><qau>South.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Relicted</ent>⟦br⟧
